<h3><font color="blue">INTRODUCTION</font></h3>
Concept cars are an expression of dreams, emotion and inspiration &ndash; and a vision of how to progress reality. Concept cars are a constant proof of how our designers and engineers are constantly probing the boundaries of their imagination and their creativity.
  Get ready to create the new paradigm of modern transportation.

 So, fire up your minds and give wings to your design.
<br/>
<br/>
<img src="file:///android_asset/ccd/Concept_Car_Vexel_by_aSoKiMoZ_resized.jpg" alt="Concept_Car_Vexel_by_aSoKiMoZ.jpg"/>

<h3><font color="blue">PROBLEM STATEMENT</font></h3>
Concept Car Design aims to provide a platform for automobile enthusiasts to showcase their ideas for a brand new concept car. So make good use of various inspirations and develop them into a coherent theme that inspires not only the form language of your vehicle but also its functionality. You are required to design a car model with a conceptual and logical idea. You can use any concept of your choice in the field of automobile like aerodynamics, transmission, etc. The design of the car should comply with the present rules of the road. The car should serve the purpose of day to day commutation without sacrificing basic luxuries. New innovations in the field of fuel economy and on road comfort are welcomed. Focusing on requirements, eco friendliness and design concept management would fetch extra points.

<h3><font color="blue">FORM OF SUBMISSION</font></h3>
<ul>
<li>	A write up in less than 1000 words describing all the details justifying your claims must be submitted</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Last date for submission of the abstract is 10th October, 2013</li>
</ul>
<ul>


<li>Send your entry to conceptcardesign@tathva.org. Include your contact number in the email.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	The selected participants will be notified through e-mail.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	A 3D model of the concept should be submitted in CAD format on the spot. Participants are expected to bring there on laptops and software. 
</li>
</ul>
<ul>

<li>	The participants will be given 15 minutes to present their paper before a panel of judges.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	10 minutes will be for presentation and 5 minutes for the Viva.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	The participant is expected to bring 3 hard copies as well as a soft copy of the paper.</li>
</ul>

<h3><font color="blue">JUDGING CRITERIA </font></h3>
     Points will be awarded based on the following criteria:<br/>
<ul>
<li>	Practicality of the design.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	Feasibility of the design.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	Implementation of modern necessities and luxuries.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	Environmental friendliness in the design.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Accuracy of parts, assembly and completeness of the model.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>	All decisions taken by the judges shall be final.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Final marks shall be based on the following format:<br/></li>
</ul>
<b>Total score</b> = 50 x <b>C</b> + 35 x <b>M</b> + 10 x <b>P</b> + 5 x <b>V</b><br/><br/>


<b>C</b> – For the concept<br/>

<b>M</b> – For the CAD model or drawings you have submitted. CAD models will be given more weightage.<br/>

<b>P</b> – Based on the presentation in front of the judges<br/>

<b>V</b> – Based on your performance in viva
Each of these will be given a score out of 10. <br/><br/>

Each participant will be given a score out of 1000 and the one with maximum total score will be declared as the winner.


<h3><font color="blue">Prizes:</font></h3>
First Prize : Rs.5000<br/>
Second Prize : Rs.3000<br/>
Third Prize : Rs.2000

<h3><font color="blue">No of participants</font></h3>
min : 1 <br>
max : 3 
